(183,1699,7,'Gibson Les Paul Standard \'50s Figured Top Electric Guitar Heritage Cherry Sunburst','The Gibson Les Paul Standard \'50s solid body electric guitar is a tribute to one of the most influential eras in music history. With its figured maple top on a solid mahogany back, this guitar delivers the unmistakable resonance and sustain that has defined the Les Paul legacy. The nitrocellulose lacquer finish enhances the natural vibrancy of its tonewoods while providing a vintage aesthetic. A rounded \'50s neck profile adds to its authentic feel, offering a comfortable grip for extended playing sessions. Combined with Burstbucker pickups and meticulous handwired electronics, this model captures the warm, punchy tones that shaped rock and roll. Every detail—from the trapezoid inlays to the ABR-1 bridge—reflects Gibson\'s dedication to craftsmanship and tone.'),
(4,2389,7,'Gibson Les Paul Modern Studio Electric Guitar Wine Red Satin','The Gibson Les Paul Modern Studio electric guitar brings contemporary appointments to a classic design. The Les Paul Modern Studio features a slim, lightweight mahogany body with a maple top that provides resonant, well-balanced tones. The guitar\'s bound ebony fingerboard tops off a compound-radius neck profile that enhances playability and comfort—from first-position chords to the highest frets. And with its player-friendly electronics, the Les Paul Modern Studio offers exceptional tonal versatility. This Les Paul includes a soft-shell case for protection and easy transport.'),
(1, 11699, 7, 'Used Gibson Tony Iommi Custom Shop SG Cherry Solid Body Electric Guitar', 'Looking for a guitar that embodies legendary tone and style? This Used Gibson Tony Iommi Custom Shop SG in stunning Cherry finish is a must-have for fans of the Black Sabbath guitarist or anyone craving a powerhouse instrument. Handcrafted to meticulous standards, this solid body electric guitar features dual signature Gibson USA Iommi humbuckers, a sleek mahogany body, and a 24-fret ebony fingerboard for smooth playability and rich, dynamic sound. The neck profile is designed for comfort, allowing you to shred with ease, while the chrome hardware and unique high-gloss finish make it as visually striking as it is sonically impressive. In great condition with only minor signs of use, this guitar maintains its exceptional playability and tonal integrity. Whether on stage or in the studio, this custom SG is your gateway to iconic heavy metal riffs and beyond.'),
(2, 2499, 7, 'Gibson \'70s Flying V Electric Guitar Classic White', 'Thee Gibson \'70s Flying V Electric Guitar Classic White is a reissue of the legendary electric guitar that helped define the sound of rock. With its striking yet comfortable asymmetrical body shape, bound rosewood fretboard and uncovered \'70s Tribute Burstbucker pickups, this Gibson Flying V provides the look and tone that shaped an era. Now with a slim taper neck for effortless soloing and available in a crisp Classic White finish with matching headstock, the Gibson \'70s Flying V offers a perfect blend of \'70s style and contemporary playability.'),
(5, 1873, 7, 'Fender American Professional II Telecaster Maple Fingerboard Electric Guitar - Butterscotch Blonde', 'The Fender American Professional II Telecaster maple fingerboard electric guitar represents the latest chapter in Fender\'s storied Telecaster lineage, blending classic design with modern refinements for today\'s players. Built with a lightweight alder body, this instrument delivers a resonant tonal foundation with balanced highs, tight lows and articulate mids. The satin-finished Deep C maple neck ensures effortless playability, while the sculpted neck heel allows seamless upper-fret access. Equipped with V-Mod II single-coil pickups, the Telecaster produces the signature twang and snap players love, enriched with enhanced clarity and warmth. A top-load/string-through bridge with compensated brass saddles offers precise intonation and versatile setup options. Whether you\'re chasing sharp, defined tones or experimenting with dynamic textures, this guitar offers the tools to shape your sound with confidence.'),
(3, 849, 7, 'Fender Player II Stratocaster Rosewood Fingerboard Electric Guitar 3-Color Sunburst', 'The Fender Player II Stratocaster electric guitar captures the iconic sound that helped define electric guitar tone—updated with modern refinements that make it one of the most versatile and player-friendly Strats yet. With its trio of Player Series Alnico 5 single-coil pickups, the Player II Strat delivers the bell-like highs, punchy mids and robust lows that have made the Stratocaster a legend among guitarists across every genre.'),
(1, 4666, 7, 'PRS Custom 24 10-Top Electric Guitar - Faded Whale Blue', 'The PRS Custom 24 10-Top electric guitar delivers impressive, versatile tone for serious players. Its flame maple top provides resonant, balanced tone with articulate highs, warm lows and rich sustain. The mahogany back and neck also enhance resonance and produce a smooth, fast playing experience. 85/15 pickups deliver a range of classic PRS tones from bright and chimey to thick and crunchy. A versatile 5-way blade switch lets you shape your tone, while the PRS stoptail bridge provides solid intonation and tuning stability. This guitar\'s stunning good looks inspire you to play your best. When you want tone and playability that matches your skill, the PRS Custom 24 10-Top belongs in your hands.');
